should participate as seems appropriate at the time in devising a
                        resolution in the Security Council which includes the condemnation of the
                        aggression;

should take no initiative to bring the question before the United Nations,
                        but should support the right of Yugoslavia or any other state to do so if it
                        desires;

should, if the question is brought before the UN, stand on the principles
                        of the Charter and support the condemnation of acts which threaten the
                        independence and integrity of Yugoslavia;

should support such appropriate action as may be taken by the General
                        Assembly, such as the use of UNSCOB for
                        observation;
